latestIgtvVideos.title: My Hair Is Me
latestIgtvVideos.caption: As a Black woman, I've always had a complicated relationship with my hair. I wore it straight for most of my life - so when I went natural I didn't even know how to do my own hair. Detangling it would take 10 hours and end up with me crying in the dark from pain, exertion, and exhaustion. It's been a long process, but I've learned to love my hair. I've learned to be grateful for my hair. I've learned to undo the belief - that was ingrained in us - that my hair wasn't "good". My hair IS Good. My hair is ME. Direction & Creative Direction: @danascruggs For @shape feat: @fall.twins, @themaryocean, @dalenkeswick, @lunamodela, @olivia_anakwe & @danusiawrites_ Connecting the dots between hair and identity. Special Thanks to @toniloggia for the assignment 🙏🏾 CD: @noahdreier / DP: @imaninikyah / Sound: Hayley Wagner / Editor: @purposefaith / Colorist: @chadwick_b_williams / Stylist: @jennbarthole / MUA: @lbcharlesbeauty / Hair: @hairbyromorgan / Post Production: @inkretouch Studio Manager: @itsgeremy #shapemagazine #myhairisme #danascruggs

latestIgtvVideos.title: How To Make It As A Photographer - The Creative Come Up w/ Dana Scruggs
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I've partnered with @hypebae and @converse to give photographers my insights on how to make it in the industry, detailed advice on how to connect with people in a position to hire you, how to monetize your creativity, and how I gained success after years of being a struggling photographer in New York. If I had this information earlier in my career, I would have been successful much faster.

latestPosts.caption:
Ariana, thank you for making the time to create with me on such a monumental day in your life ❤️

This is one image. Everything was done in-camera. 

This body of work is the result of concepts, ideas, and techniques that I’ve been developing for the past two years. 

I started testing them on a smaller scale, with just me and select models. 

Then I started testing them on a slightly larger scale, on my editorial shoots with certain celebrities. 

Then a brand gave me the support to start creating and testing these ideas in ways that pushed the work into very inspiring and unexpected directions. 

Give yourself the time and consistency to allow your imagination and your skills to catch up with each other. 

I’m so grateful to @theacademy for giving me a shot and for allowing me to bring my imagination and my skills as an Artist fully into focus. 

Huge Thanks to my photo team @marloron @hanradjawane @jeriflex & @isanstudio ❤️

Set Design: @jamiedeanstudio 

Post Production: @lilmoffet
